<% layout("/layouts/layout.ejs") %>
    <section class="landing-dashboard">
        <div>
            <video id="dashboard-video" autoplay muted loop>
                <source src="/assets/underwater1.mp4" type="video/mp4">
    
                <object data="/assets/underwater1.mp4" width="100%" height="100%">
                    <embed src="/assets/underwater1.mp4" width="100%" height="100%"></embed>
                </object>
            </video>
        </div>

        <div class="dashboard-outer-layer">
            <h1 class="brand-logo">PACE</h1>
            <p class="text-center fs-3 dashboard-brand-fullform">
                <span>Plankton</span>
                <span>Aerosol</span>
                <span>Cloud</span>
                <span>Ecosystem</span>
            </p>
            <%- include("./aboutpace.ejs") %>
        </div>
    </section>


    <section class="user-question text-center">
        <div>
            <h3 class="text-light">Ask your doubts related to PACE</h3>
            <form action="/peacewithpeace/user-questions" method="get" class="col-md-5 col-11 mx-auto">
                <div class="input-group mb-3">
                    <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter Your Doubts.(About PACE)"
                        aria-label="Username" aria-describedby="basic-addon1">
                </div>
                <button type="submit" class="btn border hover-effect">Submit</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="">
        <div class="d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center">
            <img src="https://pace.oceansciences.org/images/oci_mar2018_toward_annotated.jpg" alt="" class="col-md-4 col-12 m-5 rounded hover-effect">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-12 p-5 text-secondary">
                <p> The Ocean Color Instrument (OCI) is the primary sensor on NASA's PACE mission. It is designed to measure the color of the ocean, which is a key indicator of various biological and chemical processes. By analyzing ocean color, OCI can identify and monitor phytoplankton communities, which are microscopic plants that form the foundation of the marine food web.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-12 p-5 text-secondary">
                <p>SPEXone is being developed by a Dutch consortium consisting of SRON Netherlands Institute for Space Research (SRON) and Airbus Defence and Space Netherlands (Airbus DS NL), supported by optical expertise from the Netherlands Organisation for Applied Scientific Research.</p>
            </div>
            <img src="https://pace.oceansciences.org/images/inst_polarimeter1.png" class="col-md-4 col-12 m-5 rounded hover-effect" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="d-flex flex-wrap align-items-center">
            <img src="https://pace.oceansciences.org/images/harp2-b.png" alt="" class="col-md-4 col-12 m-5 rounded hover-effect">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-12 p-5 text-secondary">
                <p>HARP2 (Hyper-Angular Rainbow Polarimeter #2) is a wide angle imaging polarimeter designed to measure aerosol particles and clouds, as well as properties of land and water surfaces. The amount and type of particles in suspension in the atmosphere are relevant to applications pertaining to health effects, cloud life cycle and precipitation, climate, etc. </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>